PART 7: WEIGHT MULTIPLICITIES AND TOURNAMENT STRUCTURE
======================================================================

E₇ minuscule representation V(ω₇):
  All weights have multiplicity 1 (defining property of minuscule)
  56 = 2 · 28 = 2 · C(8,2)
  The 56 weights split as +28 and -28 (under the E₇ Weyl group)

The 28+28 decomposition:
  28 = C(8,2) = C(rank(E₈), 2)
  The 56-rep decomposes under E₆ ⊂ E₇ as 27 + 27' + 1 + 1
  (two copies of the 27 of E₆ plus two singlets)
  27 = dim(exceptional Jordan algebra) = C(27/1)

E₆ and the exceptional Jordan algebra:
  dim(V_E₆) = 27 (minuscule representation)
  27 = 3³ = KEY₂³
  The Jordan algebra J₃(O) has dim 27 over R
  Elements are 3×3 Hermitian matrices over octonions
  3 = KEY₂ (matrix size)
  8 = rank(E₈) (octonion dimension)
  27 = 3 + 3·8 = KEY₂ + KEY₂·rank(E₈)

27 lines on a cubic surface:
  The 27 lines form a configuration with symmetry group W(E₆)
  |W(E₆)| = 51840 = 2⁷ · 3⁴ · 5 = 2⁷ · 81 · 5
  51840 = 51840
  51840 / 720 = 72 = 72 = 8 · 9 = rank(E₈) · CS_boundary

