======================================================================

E-series dimensions: 78, 133, 248

Testing recurrence a(n) = 5a(n-1) - 6a(n-2):
  5·133 - 6·78 = 197 ≠ 248

What recurrence DO these satisfy?
Extended E-series: E₃→E₈
  Dimensions: [11, 24, 45, 78, 133, 248]

Testing a(n) = p·a(n-1) + q·a(n-2):
  E6: a(6)=2.7407·a(5)+-1.8889·a(4)
  E7: a(7)=2.0784·a(6)+-0.6471·a(5)
  E8: a(8)=-7.9394·a(7)+16.7172·a(6)

Differences between consecutive E-series dims:
  dim(E4) - dim(E3) = 24 - 11 = 13
  dim(E5) - dim(E4) = 45 - 24 = 21
  dim(E6) - dim(E5) = 78 - 45 = 33
  dim(E7) - dim(E6) = 133 - 78 = 55
  dim(E8) - dim(E7) = 248 - 133 = 115

Second differences:
  Δ²(5) = 21 - 13 = 8
  Δ²(6) = 33 - 21 = 12
  Δ²(7) = 55 - 33 = 22
  Δ²(8) = 115 - 55 = 60

Ratios:
